sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Claude
    participant Hook as governance-scan.mjs<br/>(UserPromptSubmit)
    participant Command as analyze.md<br/>(AI Reasoning)
    participant Files as Project Files

    User->>Claude: /arckit:analyze 001
    Claude->>Hook: Trigger (hooks.json matcher)
    
    Note over Hook: Phase 1: Pre-processing
    Hook->>Files: Scan projects/001-*/ artifacts
    Hook->>Files: Read all ARC-*.md files
    Hook->>Files: Scan vendors/, decisions/, reviews/
    Hook->>Hook: Extract metadata (doc type, version, status)
    Hook->>Hook: Extract requirements (REQ files)
    Hook->>Hook: Extract principles (PRIN files from 000-global)
    Hook->>Hook: Extract risks (RISK files)
    Hook->>Hook: Build cross-reference map (req IDs in designs)
    Hook->>Hook: Compute coverage (orphan requirements)
    Hook->>Hook: Scan vendor inventory + review verdicts
    Hook->>Hook: Count placeholders (TODO/TBD/TBC)
    
    Hook-->>Claude: additionalContext (15 tables + metadata)
    
    Note over Claude: Phase 2: AI Reasoning
    Claude->>Command: Execute with hook data in context
    Command->>Command: Skip Steps 1-2 (hook shortcut)
    Command->>Command: Read template for formatting
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass A: Requirements Quality
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass B: Principles Alignment
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass C: Req-Design Traceability
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass D: Vendor Procurement
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass E: Stakeholder Traceability
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass F: Risk Management
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass G: Business Case
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass H: Data Model
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass I: UK Gov Compliance
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass J: MOD SbD Compliance
    Command->>Command: Detection Pass K: Cross-Artifact Consistency
    Command->>Command: Assign severity (CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)
    Command->>Command: Generate analysis report
    Command->>Files: Write ARC-001-ANAL-v1.0.md
    
    Command-->>User: Summary (findings count, status)
